  "name": "Metronomic Hammer",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>A polished brass metronome ticks rhythmically within the haft of this <em>+1 striking gnome hooked hammer</em>. Gnome adherents of Brigh often attempt to reproduce this item as part of a ritual symbolizing methodical problem-solving and thoughtful craftsmanship.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Activate</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">r</span> envision</p>\n<p><strong>Trigger</strong> You attempt to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.ge56Lu1xXVFYUnLP]{Trip} a creature with the <em>metronomic hammer</em></p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> By timing the sweeping arcs of your Trip attempt to the built-in metronome of a <em>metronomic hammer</em>, you gain a +1 item bonus to your Athletics check to Trip the target. This item bonus increases by 1 with every subsequent Trip attempt you make with the <em>metronomic hammer</em> against the same target this turn, to a maximum of +3 on your third Trip. The bonus resets to +1 if you successfully Trip the target, if you critically fail to Trip the target, or if your turn ends.</p>"
    },
